    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix ESM status message handling for success cases\n\n### Summary\nWhen processing ESM status messages with SUCCESS cause code, the output was displaying confusing \"SUCCESS (-1)\" instead of just \"SUCCESS\". This was due to a magic number being used without proper context.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/ESM/MSG/esm_cause.h`: Added explanatory comment for ESM_CAUSE_SUCCESS magic number\n- `openair3/NAS/TEST/AS_SIMULATOR/nas_process.c`: Modified _esm_status() to handle success case specially\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Process an ESM status message with ESM_CAUSE_SUCCESS cause code\n2. Observe the output shows \"SUCCESS (-1)\" which is confusing to users\n3. After fix, output correctly shows just \"SUCCESS\"\n\nThe magic number -1 used for ESM_CAUSE_SUCCESS made the intent unclear and was error-prone for maintenance. The fix clarifies the intent with proper documentation and improves the user experience by not displaying the internal magic number value.\n"
}